Both required outputs are emitted in the working directory:

- `transcript.json` вЂ” 25 iterations, 145 hypotheses, 145 analyses; validates against `transcript_schema.json`.
- `analysis_summary.txt` вЂ” narrative synthesis organized by theme (prognostic main effects, biomarker main effects, treatment main effects, treatmentГ—biomarker interactions, demographics/socioeconomics, pharmacogenomic SNPs, supported vs. refuted hypotheses, overall conclusions).

Key findings: the cohort recovers classic prognostic signals (stage IV, ECOG, brain mets, albumin, LDH, Ki-67, weight loss) and the palbociclibГ—ER+ benefit (+1.59 mo interaction, p~1e-228). OlaparibГ—BRCA (+0.40 mo, p=0.02) and pembrolizumabГ—TNBC (+0.19 mo, p=0.015) reproduce expected biology at modest magnitude. Notably, trastuzumabГ—HER2+ is null and `her2_positive`/`her2_amplification` are statistically independent (chiВІ p=0.55) вЂ” flagged as a likely data anomaly. SNPs, comorbidities, symptom grades, and racial/insurance disparities are uniformly null; age trends positively with PFS, opposite the real-world direction.
